						<summary>

						<p>The cyclic year should correspond to A.D. 1399-1400. The inscription is slightly mutilated. It records a gift of 300 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land by a female relation of the king for offerings to god Tirumāḍappēṟuḍaiya-Nāyaṉār at Eyil which is said to be a <hi rend="italic">jīvita</hi> (of the donor).</p>						

